Example 2.10 – Solving by Cramer’s Rule
Write the system in matrix form:
\[
\begin{bmatrix}
R_1 + Ls & -Ls \\
-Ls & Ls + R_2 + \dfrac{1}{Cs}
\end{bmatrix}
\begin{bmatrix}
I_1(s) \\ I_2(s)
\end{bmatrix}
=
\begin{bmatrix}
V(s) \\ 0
\end{bmatrix}
\]
Let the determinant:
\[
\Delta =
\begin{vmatrix}
R_1 + Ls & -Ls \\
-Ls & Ls + R_2 + \dfrac{1}{Cs}
\end{vmatrix}
\]
For \(I_2(s)\), Cramer’s Rule:
\[
I_2(s) = \frac{
\begin{vmatrix}
R_1 + Ls & V(s) \\
-Ls & 0
\end{vmatrix}
}{\Delta}
= \frac{Ls\,V(s)}{\Delta}
\]

